---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Eddington ratio";
import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Eddington ratio</h1>

    <p>
      The <strong>Eddington ratio</strong> (λ_Edd) is the ratio of an AGN's bolometric luminosity to its Eddington luminosity (L_bol / L_Edd) and is a proxy for the accretion rate relative to the maximum radiative efficiency of the black hole.
    </p>

    <h2>Usage in environment studies</h2>
    <p>
      Authors often test whether AGN accretion state (λ_Edd) depends on large-scale environment. Mountrichas et al. (2026) find no significant dependence of inferred halo mass on bins of λ_Edd after matching host-galaxy properties for their X-ray BLAGN sample, implying that instantaneous accretion state is not strongly environmentally driven in this selection and redshift range<sup><a href="/pages/mountrichas_2026_agn_environments">1</a></sup>.
    </p>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Mountrichas G., Carrera F. J., Shankar F., Georgakakis A. (2026). arXiv:2603.11169.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
